cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LM, cs.CC, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with deduction modulo and the translation of higher-order logic into first-order logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of rewrite systems and congruences, which are relevant to programming language semantics. 
- cs.LM (Mathematical Logic) is another possible category as the paper deals with proof lengths and the encoding of higher-order arithmetic. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper requires the congruence to be computed in polynomial time. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of proof lengths in deduction modulo.
